            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27065",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rslootjes",
                        "name": "rslootjes",
                        "displayName": "R Slootjes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A little update\n\n{notation}\nconst SIZE_A4                = '595:842:';\nconst SIZE_A4_LANDSCAPE      = '842:595:';\n{notation}\n\nthese constants do have the notation \"x:y:\" instead of the asked  \"x:y\" notation at line 299:\n\n{notation}\nswitch (strtolower($param1)) {\n\tcase 'a4':\n\t\t$param1 = Zend_Pdf_Page::SIZE_A4;\n\t\tbreak;\n\t<-->\n\tdefault:\n\t\t\/\/ should be in \"x:y\" form\n}\n{notation}\n\nSo the comment should be changed to be \"x:y:\" or the count should be set to 2 (and then the constants need to be changed).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rslootjes",
                        "name": "rslootjes",
                        "displayName": "R Slootjes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-05T00:55:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-05T00:55:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37011",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cwt137",
                        "name": "cwt137",
                        "displayName": "Christopher Thomas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As the bug reporter said in the comment above, the right syntax is \"x:y:\". So the code should be:\r\n\r\n{code:php}\r\n$objPage = new Zend_Pdf_Page('100:100:');\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nSo this item can be closed since it is not a bug.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cwt137",
                        "name": "cwt137",
                        "displayName": "Christopher Thomas",
